# Git Commit Style Rule

When committing changes, you MUST strictly adhere to the following style:
- Write exactly **one line** per feature or fix. No multi-line commit bodies.
- Keep the summary **plain and simple**.
- No verbose literature, no apologies, and no narrative descriptions.
- Do not reference spikes, explorations, or internal docs in the commit message.
- Just mention what was actually changed or built.
